<blockquote><p>
As Governor of Mauritius, [Theodore] Hook ruled for five years before being accused of embezzling 12,000 pounds of public funds. He was dismissed from his post and returned to England, where he told friends that his dismissal was &#8216;on account of a disorder in my chest.&#8217;
</p></blockquote>
<p>&#8212; Victor Margolin, <a href="https://www.verbatimquarterly.com/back-issues/vol7_1/#the-pun-is-mightier-than-the-sword-a-short-history-of-paronomasia">&#8220;The Pun Is Mightier Than the Sword: A Short History of Paronomasia,&#8221;</a> <em>Verbatim</em>, Summer 1980</p>
